NAME
      bal connector - Generate and maintain Ballerina connector assets with AI
       assistance.

SYNOPSIS
      bal connector -h | --help
      bal connector <workflow> <command> [arguments...] [options...] [flags...]

DESCRIPTION
      The `bal connector` command provides AI-assisted workflows for generating,
       validating, documenting, and maintaining Ballerina connectors.

       Use one of the available workflows to run OpenAPI connector generation,
       Java SDK connector generation, connector catalog documentation
       generation, or visual example documentation generation.

WORKFLOWS
       openapi
             Generate and maintain Ballerina connectors from OpenAPI
             specifications.

       sdk
             Generate and maintain Ballerina connectors from Java SDKs.

       doc-generator
             Generate connector catalog documentation such as overview, setup
             guide, action reference, and trigger reference.

       example-doc
             Generate visual WSO2 Integrator example documentation with
             screenshots.

ENVIRONMENT
       ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
             Required for AI-powered workflow stages such as SDK analysis,
             OpenAPI sanitization, code repair, test generation, example
             generation, and documentation generation.

GLOBAL OPTIONS
       -h, --help
             Print help information about the `bal connector` command.

       -y, --yes
             Auto-confirm prompts where supported.

       -q, --quiet
             Reduce log output where supported.

EXAMPLES
       Run the full OpenAPI connector workflow.
             $ bal connector openapi pipeline ./openapi.yaml ./out

       Run the full SDK connector workflow.
             $ bal connector sdk pipeline example-sdk ./out

       Generate connector catalog documentation.
             $ bal connector doc-generator generate connector-name=HubSpot \
                   module-slug=hubspot package-name=ballerinax/hubspot

       Generate a visual connector example guide.
             $ bal connector example-doc connector mysql \
                   "show insert and query operations"
